# REST API Rules

## URL Design
- Resource-first, kebab-case: `/api/v1/orders`, `/api/v1/order-items`
- No verbs in URL — use HTTP method semantics
- Versioning: `/api/v1/` prefix always
- Pagination params: `?page=0&size=20&sort=createdAt,desc`

## HTTP Method Mapping
| Action | Method | URL | Response |
|--------|--------|-----|----------|
| Create | POST | `/orders` | 201 + Location header |
| Read one | GET | `/orders/{id}` | 200 |
| Read list | GET | `/orders` | 200 + Page wrapper |
| Full update | PUT | `/orders/{id}` | 200 |
| Partial update | PATCH | `/orders/{id}` | 200 |
| Delete | DELETE | `/orders/{id}` | 204 |

## Controller Pattern

```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/api/v1/orders")
@RequiredArgsConstructor
@Tag(name = "Orders", description = "Order management")
public class OrderController {

    private final OrderApplicationService orderService;

    @PostMapping
    @Operation(summary = "Create a new order")
    public ResponseEntity<OrderResponse> createOrder(
            @Valid @RequestBody CreateOrderRequest request) {
        OrderResponse response = orderService.createOrder(request);
        URI location = URI.create("/api/v1/orders/" + response.orderId());
        return ResponseEntity.created(location).body(response);
    }
}
```

## Error Response Format (MUST follow)
```json
{
  "timestamp": "2026-06-25T10:00:00Z",
  "status": 400,
  "error": "Validation Failed",
  "message": "customerId must not be blank",
  "path": "/api/v1/orders",
  "traceId": "abc123"
}
```

## Validation Rules
- Use Jakarta Bean Validation on request records
- Global `@RestControllerAdvice` handles all exceptions — no try/catch in controllers
- Domain exceptions → map to HTTP status in `GlobalExceptionHandler`

## OpenAPI
- Every endpoint has `@Operation(summary = ...)` and `@ApiResponse` annotations
- DTOs have `@Schema` field descriptions
- Generate spec at build time: `springdoc-openapi-starter-webmvc-ui`

## Checklist before PR
- [ ] URL follows resource-first, kebab-case convention
- [ ] Controller has zero business logic
- [ ] All request bodies use `@Valid`
- [ ] Error responses match standard format
- [ ] OpenAPI annotations present
- [ ] Integration test covers happy path + validation failure
